QQOOriginal event occurred {{originTime}} from source {{ source}} on DC {{target}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.ACTIVE_DORMANT.TITLE: QQOActive dormant user
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.ACTIVE_DORMANT.SUBTITLE: QQOVault user {{user}} retrieved the password of account {{account}} from CyberArk PAS after being inactive for more than {{inactiveDays}} days.
QQOVault user {{user}} retrieved the password of {{numOfAccounts}} accounts from CyberArk PAS after being inactive for more than {{inactiveDays}} days.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.ACTIVE_DORMANT.RECOMMEN: QQOMake sure that this Vault user is active, and if not, consider limiting the user's access.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.AGGREGATIVE_ICE.TITLE: QQOAnomalous access to multiple machines
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.AGGREGATIVE_ICE.SUBTITL:
QQOAccount {{account}} connected to a large number of new machines, which is unusual for this account.
These actions could indicate that the credentials of {{account}} have been abused for lateral movement.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.AGGREGATIVE_ICE.RECOMME: QQOAssess the potential damage and look for IOC:
QQOReview the accounts that have active sessions on the target machines
QQOReview the credentials stored on the target machines
QQOLook for other attack indications on the target machines
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.TITLE: QQOService Account logged on interactively
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.SUBTITLE_SIN: QQOService account {{account}} interactively logged on to {{target}} machine.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.SUBTITLE_MUL: QQOService account {{account}} interactively logged on to {{numOfMachines}} machines.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.DUAL_USAGE.RECOMMENDATI: QQOSeparate between using your service accounts and human accounts.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.GOLDEN_TICKET.TITLE: QQOGolden Ticket attack
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.GOLDEN_TICKET.SUBTITLE:
QQOA Golden Ticket attack was detected in domain {{domain}}. The attacker used a forged Kerberos ticket for account {{account}} on machine {{target}}.
This ticket originated from machine {{source}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.GOLDEN_TICKET.RECOMMEND: QQOAn attacker has compromised your domain. Carefully investigate your environment and take action to contain the attacker.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.IRREGULAR_HOUR_USER.TIT: QQOPrivileged access to the Vault during irregular hours
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.IRREGULAR_HOUR_USER.SUB:
QQOVault user {{user}} retrieved the password of privileged user {{account}} on machine {{target}} at {{startTime}}.
This action was flagged as a security event because {{user}} normally does not connect at this time.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.IRREGULAR_HOUR_USER.REC: QQOReview this Vault users activities and ensure that they are valid.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.MALICIOUS_RETRIEVAL.SUB:
QQO A potentially malicious retrieval of credentials from domain controller {{target}}, was detected on machine {{source}}.
The credentials retrieval was conducted by a successful domain controller replication.

QQOMultiple potentially malicious retrievals of credentials were detected on machine {{source}}.
The credentials retrieval was conducted by a successful domain controller replication.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.MALICIOUS_RETRIEVAL.REC:
QQOA Domain controller replication request (DCSync) must be initiated only by domain controllers.
If another authentication or management service in your network also executes domain controller replication,
it is highly recommended to protect these services at the same level as domain controllers.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.OVER_PASS_THE_HASH.SUBT:
QQOAn Overpass the Hash attack was detected in domain {{domain}}, which originated from machine {{source}}.
The attack abuses the credentials of account {{account}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.PAC_ATTACK.TITLE: QQOPAC Attack
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.PAC_ATTACK.SUBTITLE:
QQOA PAC Attack (MS14-068 exploitation) attempt was detected in domain {{domain}}, which originated from machine {{source}}.
The attacker attempted to elevate the privileges of account {{account}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.PAC_ATTACK.RECOMMENDATI: QQOMake sure that Domain Controller {{target}} is updated with patch KB3011780.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.RISKY_COMMAND.TITLE: QQOSuspicious activities detected in a privileged session
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.RISKY_COMMAND.SUBTITLE:
QQOSuspicious session activities on {{target}} were detected in a privileged session.
The session was initiated by Vault user {{user}} with account {{account}}.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.RISKY_COMMAND.RECOMMEND:
QQOReview each of the security events associated with the session and evaluate whether a response,
such as live monitoring or a manual termination of the in-progress session, is required.
QQOReview each of the security events associated with the session and assess the risk by reviewing the session's audit and recording.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.TITLE: QQOSuspected credentials theft
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.SUBTITLE_SINGLE_MAC: QQOPrivileged account {{account}} accessed {{target}} machine with a password that was not retrieved from CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.SUBTITLE_MULTI_MACH: QQOPrivileged account {{account}} accessed {{numOfMachines}} machines with a password that was not retrieved from CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.SCT.RECOMMENDATION: QQOConsider changing the passwords that were used without being retrieved.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.TITLE: QQOUnmanaged privileged account
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.SUBTITLE_SING: QQOPrivileged account {{account}} was used to access {{target}}, although this account is not managed in CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.SUBTITLE_MULT: QQOPrivileged account {{account}} was used to access {{numOfMachines}} machines, although this account is not managed in CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.UNMANAGED.RECOMMENDATIO: QQOConsider provisioning the unmanaged privileged account in CyberArk PAS.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.VAULT_IRREGULAR_IP.TITL: QQOPrivileged access to the Vault from irregular IP
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.VAULT_IRREGULAR_IP.SUBT:
QQOVault user {{user}} accessed the Vault from irregular IP {{source}}.
This action was flagged as a security event because {{user}} does not normally access the Vault from this IP.
PTA.EVENTS.CARDS.VAULT_IRREGULAR_IP.RECO: QQOReview this Vault users activities and ensure that they are valid.
